         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">12/9/91. ¶  ¶ It occurred to me in thought, dear Mr Bradshaw, that you might like me to give footnotes on the pages of the print of your treatise in reference to such plants, as you specially mention....</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">91.09.12</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Bradshaw</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Private hands.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">12/9/91.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It occurred to me in thought, dear Mr Bradshaw, that you might like me to give footnotes on the pages of the print of your treatise in reference to such plants, as you specially mention.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M published an account of the plants collected by Bradshaw during his 1891 expedition to the Kimberley region of WA in B92.05.04.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>In that case, the slips, from which you were reading,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>At a meeting of the Victorian Branch of the Royal Geographical Society, 10 September 1891 (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-variant: small-caps; ">'the royal geographical society'</seg>,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 11 September 1891, p. 3).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>should not be paged, until the notes have been added. I could make Tuesday-afternoon<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bradshaw could not have seen M at the time suggested, since the passenger list indicates that he left Melbourne for Sydney on 12 September aboard<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Cuzco</seg>, arriving on 15 September.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>free for you, if you like then to come to my place, so that you could look with me over your botanic specimens, to settle about what notes should be furnished for your memoir.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
         </div>
      </body>
